===Alternative forms===
The abbreviation of the province is 桂 (Gui), which comes from [[Guilin]], a major city in the autonomous region.

Full name Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.

===Etymology===
[[pinyin|Pinyin]] transliteration of {{etyl|cmn|en}} {{zh-l|廣西|tr=Guǎngxī}}. {{zh-l|廣|tr=guǎng}} itself means "expanse", and has been associated with the region since the creation of Guang Prefecture in 226 AD. "Guangxi" and neighbouring [[Guangdong]] literally mean "Guang West" and "Guang East". Together, Guangdong and Guangxi are called the "Two Guangs" ({{zh-l|兩廣}} ''Liǎngguǎng'').

